				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A couple specific questions about AE kiting<a name="39490"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 11 04 7:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello, I'm currently a level 60 bard, and I've been grouping 100% since probably level 10 or so. Lately, I've been experimenting with the various solo techniques some, for those times when I don't feel like grouping. I've practiced with chant kiting and fear kiting, and I'm trying to understand AE Kiting now. 
<br />

<br />
Question 1: What are the best songs to use for AE kiting at level 60? In looking at our song list, I see 3 AE detrimental songs available and 2 viable options: Denon's Disruptive Discord, and Selo's Chords of Cessation. As for Denons, according to the Song section, it does 20 damage per tick at level 65. If I'm only doing 20 damage per tick, it would seem to take weeks to kill a mob. Do I understand this right? <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Question 2: Can Selo's Chords of Cessation be used in AE Kiting? It seems to only work when I'm in melee range of a mob (meaning the mob can hit me), and the point of kiting is to stay out of melee range. So how does this work?
<br />

<br />
I've spent quite some time researching in all the forums, and I haven't seen the answers to these questions. So, please don't flame me and tell me to &quot;look in the forums.&quot; <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />  But if there is a specific link that I've missed, please share.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />

<br />
Naiku</span></td>
