			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple specific questions about AE kiting<a name="39637"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 12 04 1:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There are 4 songs at 60 to use for AE kiting: chords of dissonance (lvl 2), denon's disruptive discord (lvl 18), selo's chords of cessation (lvl 40-some, I think 47), and denon's dissention (lvl 59).  CoD and DDD only do around 20 damage BEFORE instrument mods, and the other two do more like 30 before mods.  WITH mods, however, the damages are more like 37,41,66, and 71.  Those are around the numbers I get when AEing, and I only use 2.2 mod string and brass instruments.  At 62 you get another song, Melody of Mischief, which does roughly the same damage as bereavement.  All this totals up to a little more than 200hp/tick PER mob... quite a bit when you have 30-50 mobs chasing you.
<br />

<br />
A typical AE kite can take from 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the hps of the mobs.  In nadox, for example, I could round up all the trolls and bloodtusks in the area of the lava bridge and kite them all down in about 15 minutes (including pull time) for about 50% of an AA.  This is no where near as good as other people could do, but I'm satisfied with the rate, and comfortable in the area.  
<br />

<br />
As for question 2, go to the guides section and do some reading.  No offense, but I don't see how you could miss directions on how to AE kite... most of the soloing forum discusses this and swarming. Also check the thread &quot;AE kit in PoV&quot; in the preservation forum - it has some general instructions on what to do to AE kite.  Best tip I can give is to go to a newbie yard, round everything up, and figure out a running method that keeps you close enough to hit them and have them not hit you.  For me, it's third person view running manual circles so I can adjust.  For others, it's first person running backwards.  Even more others are fond of autocircling.  Best advice is to read some and go try it... newbie trash can't kill you. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
