				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple specific questions about AE kiting<a name="39751"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 8:42 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Maybe you are practicing on the wrong types of mobs.  You want to find ones that have a small melee range.  Probably the best example of small melee mobs are the cougars in Iceclad.  A good contrast would be the ulthorks in EW.  The ulthorks and walruses can be AE'd, but their melee range is practically the 30 range on cessation and CoD.  
<br />

<br />
Some examples of things I have AE'd before:
<br />

<br />
Cougars in Iceclad
<br />
Poachers in Jaggedpine (mean backstab, but was never camped when I was there)
<br />
Anything that moved in Dulak
<br />
Torigiran Mines - everything between entrances from nadox and dulak
<br />
Trolls around lava bridge in Nadox
<br />

<br />
Even with these mobs, the distance between getting hit and not landing cessation is not much... keep at it and you'll eventually get it.</span></td>
