				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A couple specific questions about AE kiting<a name="39945"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 14 04 9:21 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In nadox, I just use run 3.  I've had run 3 since lvl 51 just so I could outrun stuff in dungeons.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I twist with my mouse when AEing, so swapping instruments as well is cake.  I just put all AE songs in my hotkey list, along with one inventory slot and my secondary slot.  To start the kite, I have my combine lute equipped (2.2 mod, best 50pp I've spent<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> ) and pick up my torin's horn ( just picked up a McVaxious horn of war last night for 500pp gogo bazaar).  Then I click the hotkey with my mouse for the first dot song, and just click around there in the hotkey bar.  Swapping the instruments out there isn't hard... I don't have to move the mouse far, and I have a 3 second window to drop the horn in and out.  The horn is only used in 1 of 5 songs (4 AE's, and Marr when needed) so it doesn't even have to be swapped much.  
<br />

<br />
I have thought about just dumping the horn out of the twist, but the extra range on that dot makes it very nice.  Maybe I'm a glutton for punishment, but I also manually run the circles.  I don't like not being in control of where I'm going. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /></span></td>
